    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''British Academics' Union Endorses Boycott of Universities in Israel'' (news article, May 31):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''British Academics' Union Endorses Boycott of Universities in Israel'' (news article, May 31):</p>
        <p>A focus on the somewhat academic question of whether the proposed boycott is acceptable because it is anti-Israel rather than anti-Semitic distracts from the more basic hypocrisy of singling out Israel for this treatment while ignoring the many countries with much more troubling human rights records.</p>
        <p>While these double standards unfortunately have become commonplace at certain United Nations institutions, one expects more from this group of British college lecturers.</p>
        <p>Daniel Wolf  Teaneck, N.J., May 31, 2007</p>
      </block>
